  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Community Based Responses to HIV in Soroti and Pallisa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the Pallisa and Soroti districts of Eastern Uganda, HIV infection rates remain high and essential services are unavailable. Stigma against people living with HIV is common and a family&#x2019;s ability to cope with the disease is severely stretched by poverty and the added burden of gender discrimination. This project aims to improve the quality of life of people living with HIV and work with them to strengthen community-based responses to the epidemic. In the shorter term, the project will develop home-based care, and support families to generate added incomes. Support groups will be run, to increase their confidence and enable them to challenge stigma and discrimination, and undertake outreach to educate the public on HIV prevention methods. In the longer term, it will advocate with the district authorities to increase HIV services available in the community, and work to reduce stigma and gender-based discrimination. It will help people to develop skills to enable people living with HIV to manage their condition better and provide support to others. This will help to make it possible for people living with HIV and their families to live a life of dignity, and contribute to local level responses to the epidemic.</narrative>
  </description>
